OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1776607869
OL,3,CGovernment to continue spending
OL,4,Ccontrols, despite #261 million surplus
OL,6,FJersey's government says it must
OL,7,Fcontinue to curb spending, despite
OL,8,Ftaking in #261 million more than it
OL,9,Fpaid out in 2025 through taxes and
OL,10,Finvestment gains.
OL,12,FThe States' Annual Report and
OL,13,FAccounts, released on Friday 17 April,
OL,14,Fshowed the Government delivered #24.7
OL,15,Fmillion in savings, despite increasing
OL,16,Fits total expenditure by more than
OL,17,F#100 million since 2024.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/5
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1776607869
OL,3,CGovernment to continue spending
OL,4,Ccontrols, despite #261 million surplus
OL,6,FThis has been achieved through
OL,7,Fmeasures such as an extended freeze on
OL,8,Fexternal public-sector hires since
OL,9,FAugust 2024, which has avoided
OL,10,Fapproximately #31 million in annual
OL,11,Fstaffing costs.
OL,13,FThe Government also slashed its Social
OL,14,FSecurity grant to just over a third of
OL,15,Fthe #77.4 million it allocated in 2024.
OL,17,FSpending on agency staff, external
OL,18,Fconsultants, and contingency labour
OL,19,Fwas cut to less than two-thirds of
OL,20,F2024 levels, down from #60 million to
OL,21,F#38 million in 2025.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/5
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1776607869
OL,3,CGovernment to continue spending
OL,4,Ccontrols, despite #261 million surplus
OL,6,FJersey's Treasury Minister, Elaine
OL,7,FMillar, says: "These results show the
OL,8,Foutcome of the work that we've focused
OL,9,Fon over the last couple of years in
OL,10,Fterms of trying to reduce government
OL,11,Fspending, reduce headcount growth, and
OL,12,Freduce consultancy spend.
OL,14,F"In the short term, we're in a very
OL,15,Fgood position, we have a strong
OL,16,Fsurplus and strong assets.
OL,18,F"In the long term, we need to keep our
OL,19,Feye on the ball and continue to
OL,20,Fcontrol our spending."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/5
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1776607869
OL,3,CGovernment to continue spending
OL,4,Ccontrols, despite #261 million surplus
OL,6,FThe report also points to work the
OL,7,FGovernment has undertaken to try and
OL,8,Fcombat cost-of-living pressures, such
OL,9,Fas a #10 reduction in face-to-face GP
OL,10,Fconsultations and free school meals in
OL,11,Fprimary schools.
OL,13,FIn 2025, the Government's total
OL,14,Fexpenditure was #1.88 billion, around
OL,15,F#105 million higher than in 2024.
OL,17,FOne of the largest increases was in
OL,18,Fsocial benefits payments, which rose
OL,19,Fby 8% to to #596 million, following a
OL,20,Fspike in claims for old-age pensions
OL,21,Fand long-term care.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/5
